body: It does say - "All optimizations are enabled by default." which is `ORT_ENABLE_ALL`

Thanks! I read that but it was not clear to me. 
Reading some issues, users are instructed to run with all optimizations. If that is the default then users must have changed that, which is not often the case.

Not sure the time frame of these issues, I think there was a time when the default was just BASIC (I think!) and perhaps then users might have been instructed to run with ALL to exercise all optimizations (and get perf gains).

But it has been ALL for some time now and if anything, it is the other way around - when users encounter a graph related exception or when users notice a diff in expected results, they are first instructed to run with NO optimizations to first establish if the issue is because of any of the graph optimizations.
That is right... initially the default was set to BASIC and therefore the suggestion used to be to enable all to get perf gains.
